</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ST. AUGUSTINE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tourists from Germany, France and
Holland have been showing up on some north Florida beaches this year
in birthday suits instead of swimsuits.
   In the past month, four of five groups of tourists who have taken
it all off have been asked to put it back on, said Sgt. Robert
Suddeth of the St. Johns County Sheriff's Office.
   Besides being unaware of local laws and customs, the tourists
generally don't speak English, making it difficult for deputies to
explain that they have to wear something in public.
   ``Once we show them the handcuffs, they generally get the
message,'' he said.
   Public nudity is punishable by a maximum fine of $1,000 and a
year in jail.
   Local citizens, both men and women, have reported the nude
beachgoers to authorities, the sergeant said.
   ``One guy said, `I don't want to do this but my wife says I have
to,''' Suddeth said.
