<FIRST>r i PM-Poland-Priest 1stLd-Writethru   07-14 0377</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Poland-Priest, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0507,0387</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Probe Death of Priest Who Harbored Killer</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Leads with 10 grafs to UPDATE with post-mortem not determining
cause of death, ADDS details on Zych and probe. Pickup 8th graf pvs, `Zych
was...</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A priest who served 3{ years in prison for
harboring a policeman's killer has been found dead, the third Polish
church leader to die in unusual circumstances in the last six
months, state media said today.
   The body of the Rev. Sylwester Zych was found early Wednesday at
a bus stop in the Baltic town of Krynica Morska, 30 miles east of
Gdansk, the official PAP news agency said.
   A preliminary post-mortem did not determine the cause of death,
and another post-mortem was to be conducted, said Solidarity
Information Service spokeswoman Malgorzata Zajaczkowska.
   Unlike the other two priests, the 39-year-old Zych was not known
as an active supporter of the Polish opposition.
   In January, the Rev. Stefan Niedzielak, a pro-independence
priest, was found dead of a broken neck in his Warsaw rectory. The
case is unsolved.
   In February, Rev. Stanislaw Suchowolec, a friend of the late Rev.
Jerzy Popieluszko, who was killed by security police in October
1984, was found dead after a fire in his home in Bialystok, 125
miles northeast of Warsaw. An investigation concluded the fire was
an accident.
   Ms. Zajaczkowska said Zych had been vacationing at the parish of
his former prison chaplain in Braniewo, 60 miles east of Krynica
Morska, and disappeared Sunday.
   According to the Solidarity Information Service in Warsaw, Zych
was not dressed in clerical clothing and had no money or documents
when he was found.
   Zych's former chaplain, identified only as Rev. Brandys, read a
newspaper item about the discovery of an unidentified corpse and
identified the body, said Ms. Zajaczkowska.
   The Roman Catholic Episcopate in Warsaw hired a helicopter to fly
to the town Thursday with a commission of church investigators.
   Zych was arrested in March 1982 and accused of helping two young
men who had shot and killed a police officer several weeks earlier
during a scuffle in a tram in Warsaw.
   Zych was sentenced to 3{ years in prison in September 1982 for
harboring one of the killers. He was released in 1986.
</TEXT>
