<FIRST>r i PM-PapandreouWedding     07-14 0315</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Papandreou Wedding,0325</SECOND>
<HEAD>Former Greek Leader Marries</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY10</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DINA KYRIAKIDOU</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>POLITIA, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Premier Andreas Papandreou, whose
loss in elections last month was blamed in part on an extramarital
affair, wed former airline attendant Dimitra Liani in a church
ceremony as hundreds of supporters cheered outside.
   The wedding Thursday night had been put off twice because
Papandreou, 70, fell ill. He was released from an Athens hospital
July 6 after two weeks of treatment for pneumonia and a kidney
ailment.
   Papandreou's relationship with Ms. Liani, 35, became public in
September when she visited him at a London hospital where he had
undergone open heart surgery.
   Papandreou was married then to the former Margaret Chant, but he
divorced his American-born wife of 38 years several days before the
June 18 elections.
   His Panhellenic Socialist Movement lost the vote amid controversy
over his personal life and a series of financial scandals.
Conservative and communist opponents allied to form an interim
government.
   About 50 people attended the Greek Orthodox ceremony at the
church of Panagia Eleftherotria in the Athens suburb of Politia.
They included ranking members of Papandreou's party, Ms. Liani's
relatives and journalists. Papandreou's four children did not attend.
   Upon arriving in a chauffeur-driven car, Papandreou waved at
hundreds of supporters who gathered at the entrance chanting ``Long
live our Andreas!''
   Minutes later, he walked into the church with Ms. Liani, who was
wearing a white strapless gown and a veil of white lace.
   The couple did not kiss as the priest declared them husband and
wife. But as they drove off, Papandreou obligingly leaned over for
photographers and kissed Ms. Liani.
   Ms. Liani divorced her husband, Alexis Kapopoulos, a
Revolutionary Greek Communist Party member, after her relationship
with Papandreou became public.
   She said in a radio interview last month the relationship had
been going on for three years.
</TEXT>
