<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--HotelFire     07-14 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Hotel Fire,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>Firemen Evacuate Downtown New Orleans Hotel; No Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A smoky mattress fire on the 17th floor of a
Marriott Hotel forced evacuation of about 50 guests and employees
Friday. No injuries were reported.
   Fire Chief William McCrossen said a mattress in a service
corridor caught fire. He said the cause was not known.
   Guests were required to use the stairs to evacuate the building,
which is on the edge of New Orleans' French Quarter.
   ``I had to walk down 19 floors with this baby,'' said Catherine
DeBault of Beaumont, Texas, who was with her 5-month-old daughter.
She said the child has a heart condition but suffered no apparent
harm.
   The fire chief credited a sprinkler system, smoke detectors and
an air-tight stairwell for confining the blaze, and called the
damage minimal.
</TEXT>
