<HEAD>Former Izvestia Editor Dies at Age 70</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lev N. Tolkunov, who twice served as editor of the
government newspaper Izvestia and a member of the Communist Party
Central Committee, has died at age 70, Tass reported Friday.
   After holding senior posts in the Central Committee, Tolkunov
became editor of Izvestia in 1965, was appointed chairman of the
semi-official Novosti Press Agency 1976-83, then was restored to the
more prestigious Izvestia post for a year.
   From 1984 to 1988, he served as chairman of the Soviet of the
Union, one of two houses in the Soviet parliament that was
reconstituted this year.
