<HEAD>Hundreds Of Marcos Supporters Rally Near U.S. Embassy</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto MLA1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of supporters of Ferdinand
Marcos protested in front of the U.S. Embassy on Friday to renew
demands for the return of the ousted president.
   The protesters hold almost weekly rallies near the embassy. They
accuse U.S. authorities of kidnapping Marcos and his family after he
was ousted in a popular military uprising in February 1986 that
