light trucks jumped 8.9 percent over the same period last year, the
companies report.
   The eight major U.S.-based automakers reported Thursday that they
sold vehicles at an average rate of 35,614 a day during the July
1-10 period this year compared with a rate of 32,696 during the same
time last year. Car sales were up 9.3 percent and truck sales rose
8.3 percent.
</TEXT>
