<FILEID>AP-NR-07-14-89 1023EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet10am     07-14 0330</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 10am,0347</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market edged upward today in a hesitant
response to a fresh barrage of statistics on the state of the
economy.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 5.88 to 2,544.20 in
the first half hour of trading.
   Gainers held a narrow lead over losers in the early tally of New
York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 366 up, 341 down and 517
unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 27.09 million shares as of 10
a.m. on Wall Street.
   Several reports from the government this morning lent support to
the widespread view that the pace of economic activity was
continuing to slow, fulfilling a primary goal of the Federal
Reserve's credit policy.
   The Fed reported a 0.2 percent drop in industrial production for
June, and a decline in capacity utilization at the nation's
factories, utilities and mines.
   Separately, the Labor Department said its producer price index of
finished goods dropped 0.1 percent last month. That number came in
below advance estimates calling for an increase of between 0.1 and
0.3 percent.
   However, the producer price index, excluding its sometimes
volatile food and energy components, was up 0.7 percent. That left
market participants without an unequivocal signal of slackening
inflationary pressures, analysts said.
   Among actively traded blue chips, Eastman Kodak rose \ to 49 and
General Motors gained ] to 42], but International Business Machines
dropped [ to 114} and DuPont was down \ at 112\.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
.22 to 184.53. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up .26 at 367.90.
   On Wednesday the Dow Jones industrial average rose 5.69 to
2,538.32, extending its gain so far this month to 98.26 points.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 7 to 6 on the
NYSE, with 789 up, 661 down and 527 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 153.80 million shares, against 160.55
million in the previous session.
