<FIRST>r f AM-WhirlpoolLayoffs     07-14 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Whirlpool Layoffs,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>Whirlpool To Lay Off 850 Workers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT SMITH, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Citing declines in demand for
refrigerators, Whirlpool Corp. plans to lay off 850 employees next
month.
   The layoffs, scheduled for Aug. 14, will leave Whirlpool's
payroll at about 2,750 in Fort Smith, where the plant ranked as the
largest local employer and the third-biggest manufacturer in
Arkansas.
   Last summer, the payroll was about 5,400, officials said.
   But the company, based in Benton Harbor, Mich., began laying off
employees because of what was described as slumping demand for its
products. Last August, Whirlpool said it would cut its payroll to
about 3,000 workers by February 1990.
   Whirlpool said Thursday the latest reductions were necessary
because of declines in sales of side-by-side and top-mounted
refrigerator-freezers to Sears Roebuck and Co., Whirlpool's largest
customer.
</TEXT>
