<FILEID>AP-NR-07-14-89 1957EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-Grace     07-14 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Grace,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>W.R. Grace Reports Lower Second Quarter Results</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   W.R. Grace &amp; Co. reported Friday a 31.5 percent
drop in second-quarter earnings, reflecting higher interest expenses.
   For the three-month period ended June 30, Grace's after-tax
income totaled $44.07 million, or 52 cents a share, down from $64.4
million, or 76 cents a share, in the comparable 1988 period.
   Revenue of the New York-based specialty chemicals company rose
4.4 percent to $1.51 billion from $1.45 billion a year earlier.
   Company Chairman J. Peter Grace attributed the earnings decline
partly to higher interest expense and projected an improvement in
the second half.
   ``Despite these lower figures for the quarter, we remain
optimistic that full year income will exceed the $2.26 per share
reported for 1988,'' Grace said.
   For the first six months of 1989, Grace's profit fell 31.7
percent to $73.5 million, or 86 cents a share, from $107.52 million,
or $1.27 a share, in the year-earlier quarter.
   The company's revenue in the first half totaled $2.91 billion, up
6 percent from $2.74 billion a year ago.
</TEXT>
